Children.Name: Message
Children.Value: "This program cannot be run in DOS mode.\r\r\n$"

Children.Name: NumberOfSections
Children.Description: Number of sections; indicates size of the Section Table, which immediately follows the headers.

Children.Name: TimeDateStamp
Children.Description: Time and date the file was created in seconds since January 1st 1970 00:00:00 or 0.

Children.Name: OptionalHeader
Children.Description: Size Size of the optional header, the format is described below.

Children.Name: Characteristics
Children.Description: Flags indicating attributes of the file, see §II.25.2.2.1.

Children.Name: CodeSize
Children.Description: Size of the code (text) section, or the sum of all code sections if there are multiple sections.

Children.Name: InitializedDataSize
Children.Description: Size of the initialized data section, or the sum of all such sections if there are multiple data sections.

Children.Name: UninitializedDataSize
Children.Description: Size of the uninitialized data section, or the sum of all such sections if there are multiple unitinitalized data sections.

Children.Name: EntryPointRVA
Children.Description: RVA of entry point , needs to point to bytes 0xFF 0x25 followed by the RVA in a section marked execute/read for EXEs or 0 for DLLs

Children.Name: BaseOfCode
Children.Description: RVA of the code section. (This is a hint to the loader.)

Children.Name: BaseOfData
Children.Description: RVA of the data section. (This is a hint to the loader.)

Children.Name: SectionAlignment
Children.Description: Shall be greater than File Alignment.

Children.Name: ImageSize
Children.Description: Size, in bytes, of image, including all headers and padding; shall be a multiple of Section Alignment.

Children.Name: HeaderSize
Children.Description: Combined size of MS-DOS Header, PE Header, PE Optional Header and padding; shall be a multiple of the file alignment.

Children.Name: SubSystem
Children.Description: Subsystem required to run this image. Shall be either IMAGE_SUBSYSTEM_WINDOWS_CUI (0x3) or IMAGE_SUBSYSTEM_WINDOWS_GUI (0x2).

Children.Name: ImportTable
Children.Description: RVA and Size of Import Table, (§II.25.3.1).

Children.Name: BaseRelocationTable
Children.Description: Relocation Table; set to 0 if unused (§).

Children.Name: ImportAddressTableDirectory
Children.Description: RVA and Size of Import Address Table,(§II.25.3.1).

Children.Name: CLIHeader
Children.Description: CLI Header with directories for runtime data,(§II.25.3.1).

Children.Name: Name
Children.Description: An 8-byte, null-padded ASCII string. There is no terminating null if the string is exactly eight characters long.

Children.Name: VirtualSize
Children.Description: Total size of the section in bytes. If this value is greater than SizeOfRawData, the section is zero-padded.

Children.Name: VirtualAddress
Children.Description: For executable images this is the address of the first byte of the section, when loaded into memory, relative to the image base.

Children.Name: SizeOfRawData
Children.Description: Size of the initialized data on disk in bytes, shall be a multiple of FileAlignment from the PE header. If this is less than VirtualSize the remainder of the section is zero filled. Because this field is rounded while the VirtualSize field is not it is possible for this to be greater than VirtualSize as well. When a section contains only uninitialized data, this field should be 0.

Children.Name: PointerToRawData
Children.Description: Offset of section's first page within the PE file. This shall be a multiple of FileAlignment from the optional header. When a section contains only uninitialized data, this field should be 0.

Children.Name: Characteristics
Children.Description: Flags describing section’s characteristics; see below.

Children.Name: Cb
Children.Description: Size of the header in bytes

Children.Name: MajorRuntimeVersion
Children.Description: The minimum version of the runtime required to run this program, currently 2.

Children.Name: MinorRuntimeVersion
Children.Description: The minor portion of the version, currently 0.

Children.Name: MetaData
Children.Description: RVA and size of the physical metadata (§II.24).

Children.Name: EntryPointToken
Children.Description: Token for the MethodDef or File of the entry point for the image

Children.Name: Resources
Children.Description: RVA and size of implementation-specific resources.

Children.Name: StrongNameSignature
Children.Description: RVA of the hash data for this PE file used by the CLI loader for binding and versioning

Children.Name: VTableFixups
Children.Description: RVA of an array of locations in the file that contain an array of function pointers (e.g., vtable slots), see below.

Children.Name: Data
Children.Description: Type is stored in high 4 bits of word, type IMAGE_REL_BASED_HIGHLOW (0x3). Offset stored in remaining 12 bits of word. Offset from starting address specified in the Page RVA field for the block. This offset specifies where the fixup is to be applied.
